# =============================================================================
# Setting Up Oracle Cloud Backend
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Create a Bucket in Oracle Cloud:
#    - Go to OCI Console > Storage > Object Storage
#    - Create a bucket named "cognive-terraform-state"
#    - Note your namespace (shown in bucket details)
#
# 2. Create Customer Secret Keys:
#    - Go to OCI Console > Identity > Users > Your User
#    - Under "Resources", click "Customer Secret Keys"
#    - Generate a new key pair
#    - Save the Access Key and Secret Key
#
# 3. Set Environment Variables:
#    export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="<your-access-key>"
#    export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="<your-secret-key>"
#
# 4. Find Your Namespace:
#    - Go to OCI Console > Administration > Tenancy Details
#    - Copy the "Object Storage Namespace"
#
# 5. Construct the Endpoint:
#    https://<namespace>.compat.objectstorage.<region>.oraclecloud.com
#    
#    Example regions:
#    - us-ashburn-1 (US East)
#    - us-phoenix-1 (US West)
#    - eu-frankfurt-1 (Germany)
#    - ap-tokyo-1 (Japan)
#
